description:
Task 3.5 from PRD Phase 3: Architecture Modernization

Create AppError sealed class with localizedMessage(AppLocalizations l10n) method enabling i18n-ready error messages. This is the bridge between Phase 3 (architecture) and Phase 4 (i18n).

Example:
  sealed class AppError {
    String localizedMessage(AppLocalizations l10n);
  }
  class NetworkError extends AppError {
    String localizedMessage(l10n) => l10n.errorNoInternet;
  }
  class AuthError extends AppError {
    final AuthErrorCode code;
    String localizedMessage(l10n) => switch (code) {
      AuthErrorCode.invalidCredentials => l10n.errorInvalidCredentials,
      ...
    };
  }

## Files Affected
- New: `lib/core/errors/app_error.dart`
- Provider files (update to use AppError)

## Issues Addressed
- L11: Structured error types needed for i18n-ready messages

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] AppError sealed class created with localizedMessage(AppLocalizations l10n) method
- [ ] NetworkError, AuthError, ServerError, SubscriptionError subclasses created
- [ ] Each error type maps to appropriate l10n keys
- [ ] Providers use AppError instead of raw e.toString()
- [ ] Error messages are localizable (no hardcoded English in error presentation)
- [ ] Exhaustive pattern matching on AppError in UI layer

## Quality Gates
- [ ] `flutter analyze` passes for all affected files
- [ ] No raw exception strings shown to users

