Rewrite `currentThemeDataProvider` in `lib/app/theme/theme_provider.dart` to derive theme data
from `settingsProvider` instead of the dead `themeProvider`.

Fixes BUG-1 (disconnected state systems), BUG-4 (cosmetic dynamicColor toggle).

## Implementation

Replace the current `currentThemeDataProvider` with:

```dart
final currentThemeDataProvider = Provider<ThemeDataPair>((ref) {
  final asyncSettings = ref.watch(settingsProvider);
  final settings = asyncSettings.valueOrNull ?? const AppSettings();
  final dynamicColors = ref.watch(dynamicColorProvider);

  final ThemeData lightTheme;
  final ThemeData darkTheme;

  switch (settings.themeMode) {
    case AppThemeMode.materialYou:
      final useDynamic = settings.dynamicColor;
      lightTheme = materialYouLightTheme(
        dynamicColorScheme: useDynamic ? dynamicColors.light : null,
      );
      darkTheme = materialYouDarkTheme(
        dynamicColorScheme: useDynamic ? dynamicColors.dark : null,
      );
    case AppThemeMode.cyberpunk:
      lightTheme = cyberpunkLightTheme();
      darkTheme = cyberpunkDarkTheme(oled: settings.oledMode);
  }

  final themeMode = switch (settings.brightness) {
    AppBrightness.system => ThemeMode.system,
    AppBrightness.light => ThemeMode.light,
    AppBrightness.dark => ThemeMode.dark,
  };

  return ThemeDataPair(light: lightTheme, dark: darkTheme, themeMode: themeMode);
});
```

Key changes:
- Watch `settingsProvider` instead of `themeProvider`
- Use `AppThemeMode` from `app_settings.dart` (not the duplicate in `theme_provider.dart`)
- Gate `dynamicColors` on `settings.dynamicColor` flag (fixes BUG-4)
- Use `AppBrightness` enum from `app_settings.dart`
- Fall back to `const AppSettings()` while `AsyncValue` is loading

## Files to Modify
- `lib/app/theme/theme_provider.dart` -- rewrite `currentThemeDataProvider`

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `currentThemeDataProvider` watches `settingsProvider` (not `themeProvider`)
- [ ] Changing theme mode via `settingsProvider` immediately updates the `ThemeDataPair`
- [ ] `dynamicColors` are only passed when `settings.dynamicColor == true`
- [ ] OLED mode is passed to `cyberpunkDarkTheme(oled:)` from settings
- [ ] `ThemeDataPair` includes correct `themeMode` based on `settings.brightness`
- [ ] No compile errors (`flutter analyze` passes)

## Quality Gates
- [ ] `cd /home/beep/projects/VPNBussiness/cybervpn_mobile && flutter analyze` passes

Add one-time migration logic to `SettingsRepositoryImpl.getSettings()` that reads legacy System A
SharedPreferences keys (`theme_mode`, `theme_brightness`, `theme_oled_mode`) and migrates their
values to the System B keys (`settings.themeMode`, `settings.brightness`, `settings.oledMode`),
then cleans up the legacy keys.

This ensures existing users do not lose their theme preferences after the update.

## Implementation

In `lib/features/settings/data/repositories/settings_repository_impl.dart`, add to `getSettings()`:

```dart
// Migrate legacy theme keys (one-time)
if (!_prefs.containsKey(_kThemeMode)) {
  final legacyMode = _prefs.getString('theme_mode');
  if (legacyMode != null) {
    await _prefs.setString(_kThemeMode, legacyMode);
    await _prefs.setString(_kBrightness, _prefs.getString('theme_brightness') ?? 'system');
    await _prefs.setBool(_kOledMode, _prefs.getBool('theme_oled_mode') ?? false);
    // Clean up legacy keys
    await _prefs.remove('theme_mode');
    await _prefs.remove('theme_brightness');
    await _prefs.remove('theme_oled_mode');
  }
}
```

## Files to Modify
- `lib/features/settings/data/repositories/settings_repository_impl.dart`

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Migration runs only when `settings.themeMode` key does NOT exist in SharedPreferences
- [ ] Legacy `theme_mode` value is copied to `settings.themeMode`
- [ ] Legacy `theme_brightness` value is copied to `settings.brightness` (default `system`)
- [ ] Legacy `theme_oled_mode` value is copied to `settings.oledMode` (default `false`)
- [ ] All 3 legacy keys are removed after migration
- [ ] Migration is idempotent (running twice does not corrupt data)
- [ ] If no legacy keys exist, migration is a no-op
- [ ] `flutter analyze` passes

